data.title: Good Breakfast & Lunch
data.text: This is a local place and you will find it full of locals on any day of the week.  They are open for breakfast and lunch.  Nice omelettes and your usual breakfast fare.  Lunch is also very good with the burgers being a favorite.  Prices are very reasonable and the food is fresh and good.

data.title: Horrible service, average food.
data.text:
We saw so many great reviews about this place, we were dying to try it. We stopped in one day for breakfast on our way to Disney. The first thing we are greeted by is a sign on the door that they don't accept cards. Great. Hubby walked over to Wells Fargo and got hammered in ATM fees to get cash so we could try this delicious restaurant.

There were a lot of regulars in the place and our server was talking to all of them. But, short with us. It was "what would you like to drink" and "are you ready to order" and not even with a smile, guess we were taking her away from her conversations with the people who somehow managed to get to know her. 

The menu was not very big, it's very basic when it comes to offerings. But, we placed an order. It didn't take long for the food to come out, but when she brought it to the table she really just dumped it and left, guess we were interfering with her conversation again by ordering our meal. I had to flag her down to get condiments. And a refill never came. 

Later I started wondering if the server may have been the owner, she ended up digging into a pile of cash to make some change. 

I hope the regulars don't die or move away because they aren't doing anything to gain new customers. I know we won't be back.

data.title: Nothing great but it's edible
data.text: This place had such great reviews- did we go on a bad day??  Our server was very nice and took good care of us but our breakfasts were just breakfast.  I asked for crisp bacon, as I always do, and I always say that they can burn it if they want, I just can handle chewy bacon.  Well, I got chewy bacon and sent it back to be crisped up.  If we are ever in the Deltona area again, we will find somewhere else to go.

data.title: Good Eats Diner
data.text: Its a small hole in the wall place with indoor and outdoor seating. Very small inside, not a lot of tables. Waitresses are nice and friendly but a little on the slow side. They are open 6-2pm seven days a week. They serve breakfast and lunch.  Food was average, I did not like the home fries they had a slightly different taste to them then i am used to when having breakfast.

data.title: Good owner , very friendly , treats you like your important, royal service. WARM
data.text: Received special order , like  it is normal. Had a very nice talk with me . I have been at this diner about ten times this year.  They treat me like family. I feel very warm inside when i am at this diner.

data.title: Another accidental find
data.text: Nice little diner. Found while looking for another. Seemed to have good attendance and we were hungry. First off - CASH only. Open for breakfast and lunch. Breakfast menu looked great. I would definitely do that after having lunch. I had the liver/onions with mashed potatoes and gravy and green beans ($6.50). The liver was perfectly cooked (for me-I like it a little med-rare) The mashed - good but tasted like a batch made a lot earlier in the day - still delicious with the gravy. My companion had a BLT with extra bacon - ($4.25 - $1.00 extra bacon). She said the fruit cocktail was good and plentiful french fries ($1.50). We had a great lunch. Friendly folks and we will come back again next time DeLand has a dog show.

data.title: Good Home Cooking in a "PINCH"!
data.text: Friendly staff, good breakfast and lunch! We have now been here trice. Once for breakfast and once for lunch. " BIG Burgers"> Just do not be in a rush. It is also only open breakfast & Lunch. Closes at !:)) ishhhhhhhh!

data.title: The name says it all!
data.text: Bring cash because they don't accept plastic! No fuss, nothing fancy-just good food & great company. Everyone is so friendly- you feel like family- even the other customers welcome you! The menu is filled with plenty of good old fashioned meals like egg salad, burgers, chicken, tuna salad and all kinds of egg dishes. Who doesn't love breakfast foods all day? But what really keeps me coming back is the price! Where can 4 people eat for like $20 bucks and get GOOD food? Even the greasy fast food places are like $7-$8 per person for junk! I just wish they were open for dinner & late night munchies!

data.title: Breakfast  & Lunch At Its Best
data.text: This mom and pop diner has quite a crowd for breakfast and it's easy to see why.  We visited this location this past Sunday and all the tables were filled including the ones outside.  The food is great and the prices are low which adds up to a great value when eating out.  The only drawback is the fact that this a cash only business and no credit cards are honored.  The diner is open everyday at 6:00 A.M.   If you are in the area stop in for a memorable breakfast that cost you very little.

data.title: Mom &  Pop Family Style Diner
data.text: This diner serves the locals quite well which makes it a family like atmosphere.  The menu covers all the bases for a quick breakfast or lunch in a tranquil setting.  The homemade soup was just great but I did not have room for one of the daily specials which are posted.  Only drawback is the cash only pay option.  If you are in the area and want to eat and relax, try this diner out and enjoy.
